        <bioghist id="ref3">
            <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
            <p>Rembrandt Peale was a portrait and historical painter. He was the son of Charles Willson Peale.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <odd id="ref13">
            <head>Early American History Note</head>
            <p>This volume contains some sketches Rembrandt Peale made in the 1850s. Some are in pencil while others appear to be watercolor. Many depict landscapes or the natural world. There is a very nice image of the Delaware Water Gap.</p>
        </odd>
